<statement>
<p>If a right triangle has legs of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={15}</m> and <m>\displaystyle{b}={25}</m>, what are the angles</p>
<p>
  opposite from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}</m>: <m>\displaystyle{A}=</m> <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 2" class="text"/><circumflex/><m>\displaystyle\circ</m> </p>
<p>
  opposite from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}</m>: <m>\displaystyle{B}=</m> <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 2" class="text"/><circumflex/><m>\displaystyle\circ</m> </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>31</li><li>59</li></ul></p><p>For angle <m>\displaystyle{A}</m> the opposite side has length <m>\displaystyle{a}={15}</m> and the adjacent side has length <m>\displaystyle{b}={25}</m>. The angle is therefore</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={\arctan{{\left(\frac{{15}}{{25}}\right)}}}\approx{30.963756532074}^{\circ}\approx{31}^{\circ}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle <m>\displaystyle{B}</m> the opposite side has length <m>\displaystyle{b}={25}</m> and the adjacent side has length <m>\displaystyle{a}={15}</m>. The angle is therefore</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arctan{{\left(\frac{{25}}{{15}}\right)}}}\approx{59.036243467926}^{\circ}\approx{59}^{\circ}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>